Description of female terminalia.
Posterior margin of T5 elliptical, brown, with golden microtrichosity dorsally and silver spots laterally (
Figs 42–44
). T6 divided into two halves, orange with a row of setae near posterior margin. Spiracle 6 located on intersegmentary membrane, spiracle 7 located on T6. T8 absent (
Fig. 39
). Epiproct undivided, covered with long and fine setae. Cercus covered with long and fine setae. Hypoproct represented by a triangular membranous area covered with fine, long setae (
Fig. 40
). ST6 rectangular, covered with setulae and with a row of setae near posterior margin. ST7 square, with fine small setae near posterior margin. ST8 triangular, covered with fine small setae (
Fig. 39
). Spermathecae rounded (
Fig. 41
).
